How is that
even possible?

1226
01:18:00,094 --> 01:18:02,388
I haven't the faintest idea.

1227
01:18:02,763 --> 01:18:04,098
<i>Alex.</i>

1228
01:18:30,583 --> 01:18:32,960
<i>Alex, please return
to the station.</i>

1229
01:18:34,003 --> 01:18:35,796
I wanna run some tests.

1230
01:18:36,630 --> 01:18:38,299
Well, this should
be interesting.

1231
01:18:55,316 --> 01:18:56,483
MURPHY: <i>And your phone
on the table!</i>

1232
01:18:56,609 --> 01:18:58,819
We're not cops, all right?
We work for Antoine Vallon.

1233
01:18:58,986 --> 01:19:01,196
LEWIS: Whoa!
MURPHY: What'd you say?

1234
01:19:01,989 --> 01:19:03,824
We work for Antoine Vallon.

1235
01:19:28,891 --> 01:19:30,142
(GLASS SHATTERS)
(GROANS)

1236
01:19:30,225 --> 01:19:31,602
(SCREAMING)

1237
01:19:32,686 --> 01:19:33,979
My hand, man!

1238
01:19:34,063 --> 01:19:35,230
Where's Antoine Vallon?

1239
01:19:35,356 --> 01:19:36,565
You broke my hand, man!

1240
01:19:37,358 --> 01:19:39,234
I know you
remember me, Jerry.

1241
01:19:39,944 --> 01:19:41,362
(BONES CRACKING)
(SCREAMING)

1242
01:19:43,280 --> 01:19:44,448
Where's Vallon?

1243
01:19:44,531 --> 01:19:45,616
Wait a minute.

1244
01:19:45,699 --> 01:19:47,868
If I tell you where Vallon
is, he'll kill my wife
and kid, man.

1245
01:19:49,995 --> 01:19:53,248
Your wife left you in 2019
after filing charges
for domestic abuse.

1246
01:19:53,332 --> 01:19:55,209
And you don't have a kid.

1247
01:19:55,668 --> 01:19:56,627
But I do.

1248
01:19:56,710 --> 01:19:58,170
(SCREAMING)

1249
01:19:58,253 --> 01:19:59,505
I'm not askin' again!

1250
01:19:59,672 --> 01:20:01,757
Look, I swear, man.
I don't know where
Vallon is, okay?

1251
01:20:01,924 --> 01:20:05,260
The only guy I talk to
is his driver Marcus.
That's it, man. That's it!

1252
01:20:05,844 --> 01:20:07,721
Does he have a phone number?

1253
01:20:24,071 --> 01:20:27,282
We have a problem.
Alex is breaking protocol.

1254
01:20:27,449 --> 01:20:28,450
What's he doing?

1255
01:20:28,617 --> 01:20:30,744
He's off solving
his own murder.

1256
01:20:30,911 --> 01:20:33,664
Oh, that is genius.

1257
01:20:34,081 --> 01:20:35,708
Why didn't I think of that?

1258
01:20:42,756 --> 01:20:44,258
VALLON: <i>How long
till he gets here?</i>

1259
01:20:44,425 --> 01:20:46,427
WOMAN: <i>Five minutes.</i>
All right.

1260
01:20:46,802 --> 01:20:48,470
Johnny, you stay
on these monitors.

1261
01:20:48,637 --> 01:20:49,930
JOHNNY: What happened?

1262
01:20:51,223 --> 01:20:53,934
Some idiot used
an unencrypted phone.

1263
01:20:55,269 --> 01:20:56,395
MARCUS: Shit.

1264
01:21:04,653 --> 01:21:06,280
All right, everyone,
listen up!

1265
01:21:06,655 --> 01:21:07,948
He's coming.

1266
01:21:08,115 --> 01:21:10,951
He leaves alive, you don't.

1267
01:21:12,119 --> 01:21:13,787
MAN: How do we stop him?

1268
01:21:15,164 --> 01:21:18,333
.50 caliber and above.
Aim for the head.

1269
01:21:27,968 --> 01:21:29,136
(BEEP)

1270
01:21:30,304 --> 01:21:31,805
This one's set.

1271
01:21:32,097 --> 01:21:33,265
Let's go. Go!
(BEEPING)

1272
01:21:33,432 --> 01:21:34,767
All right, move! Let's go!

1273
01:21:36,143 --> 01:21:37,978
Come on. Come on!

1274
01:21:39,772 --> 01:21:40,773
Ready to go!

1275
01:21:41,815 --> 01:21:43,150
They're all set.

1276
01:21:44,151 --> 01:21:45,444
(POWERING DOWN)

1277
01:21:49,615 --> 01:21:51,492
(MOTORCYCLE APPROACHING)

1278
01:21:53,285 --> 01:21:54,870
(GUNS COCKING)

1279
01:22:49,091 --> 01:22:50,217
(SCREAMS)
(SHELLS CLATTERING)

1280
01:23:11,113 --> 01:23:12,406
Finish it!

1281
01:23:18,662 --> 01:23:19,746
(GROANS)

1282
01:23:26,795 --> 01:23:28,088
You freak, die!

1283
01:23:37,639 --> 01:23:38,640
(SCREAMING)

1284
01:23:41,810 --> 01:23:43,437
(HEAVY FOOTSTEPS)

1285
01:24:11,423 --> 01:24:13,467
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

1286
01:24:17,346 --> 01:24:18,639
Watch out.

1287
01:24:18,972 --> 01:24:20,432
LEWIS: Need me
to call a doctor?

1288
01:24:20,599 --> 01:24:22,601
Come on, Jack.
You're gonna like this.

1289
01:24:25,312 --> 01:24:26,396
What the hell
you doin' here?

1290
01:24:26,480 --> 01:24:27,773
Y'all gonna play
good cop, bad cop?

1291
01:24:27,856 --> 01:24:30,567
Nah, Daniels.
Bad cop, RoboCop.

1292
01:24:32,527 --> 01:24:35,656
ROBOCOP: I've recovered
26 guns from
Vallon's warehouse.

1293
01:24:35,822 --> 01:24:38,617
Thirteen serial numbers
match weapons
missing from Evidence.

1294
01:24:38,784 --> 01:24:40,619
And I got your prints
all over 'em.

1295
01:24:40,786 --> 01:24:41,787
This is bullshit.

1296
01:24:41,954 --> 01:24:43,747
ROBOCOP: I also
have CCTV footage

1297
01:24:43,830 --> 01:24:45,832
of you and Vallon
the same day
he tried to kill me.

1298
01:24:45,999 --> 01:24:48,168
VALLON: <i>So put him</i>
<i>on the payroll. Why</i>
<i>we talkin' about this?</i>

1299
01:24:48,335 --> 01:24:51,630
DANIELS: <i>It won't work.</i>
<i>Now that his partner got hit,</i>
<i>he's never gonna let it go.</i>

1300
01:24:51,797 --> 01:24:53,215
VALLON: <i>What is that?</i>
LAKE: <i>Lewis' hospital.</i>

1301
01:24:53,382 --> 01:24:54,841
<i>Murphy's dropping by
this afternoon.</i>

1302
01:24:55,008 --> 01:24:57,886
<i>I kill a cop, I'm lookin'
over my shoulder...</i>

1303
01:24:58,053 --> 01:25:00,347
You know what they do
to cops in prison, man?

1304
01:25:00,806 --> 01:25:03,392
Being locked up
with the same dudes
you put in there?

1305
01:25:06,728 --> 01:25:08,438
How long you think
before he gives you up?

1306
01:25:09,064 --> 01:25:10,232
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

1307
01:25:12,192 --> 01:25:14,861
Don't shoot me. Okay?

1308
01:25:15,862 --> 01:25:18,198
I swear to Christ.
It was Dean.

1309
01:25:18,365 --> 01:25:21,243
She helped pull those guns.
Just don't shoot me.

1310
01:25:23,203 --> 01:25:25,205
Thank you
for your cooperation.

1311
01:25:26,164 --> 01:25:27,249
(SCREAMS)

1312
01:25:27,332 --> 01:25:28,875
You can cuff him now, Jack.

1313
01:25:37,968 --> 01:25:39,845
Now I know why we
couldn't get an arrest.

1314
01:25:41,179 --> 01:25:43,265
'Cause Vallon was protected
from up on high.

1315
01:25:43,348 --> 01:25:45,058
Alex, I can explain.

1316
01:25:45,726 --> 01:25:47,102
You tipped
him off today.

1317
01:25:47,185 --> 01:25:48,437
Come on, man.
Don't do this.

1318
01:25:48,520 --> 01:25:50,439
You tried to kill me twice.

1319
01:25:50,522 --> 01:25:53,817
I trusted you.
And you destroyed my family.

1320
01:25:54,109 --> 01:25:55,110
Confess.

1321
01:25:56,445 --> 01:25:58,113
Now, in front of everyone.

1322
01:25:58,238 --> 01:25:59,239
Confess!

1323
01:26:03,160 --> 01:26:04,578
(PEOPLE GASP)

1324
01:26:09,082 --> 01:26:10,083
What happened?

1325
01:26:10,250 --> 01:26:12,377
Tin Man is down.
Had to be done.

1326
01:26:12,544 --> 01:26:13,545
<i>Why?</i>

1327
01:26:13,712 --> 01:26:14,963
Product shot a corrupt cop.

1328
01:26:15,047 --> 01:26:16,506
Two more seconds,
the chief's brains

1329
01:26:16,590 --> 01:26:19,092
would've been splattered
across the 6:00 news.

1330
01:26:19,551 --> 01:26:20,635
We got anything on her?

1331
01:26:20,802 --> 01:26:23,138
Well, she's the Chief of
the Detroit Police Department.

1332
01:26:23,221 --> 01:26:25,098
What do you think?

1333
01:26:28,935 --> 01:26:30,228
You know what?

1334
01:26:31,646 --> 01:26:34,900
This might actually
tip this thing
right into the net.

1335
01:26:41,323 --> 01:26:44,493
NOVAK ON TV:
<i>Alex, I don't know</i>
<i>if you can hear me.</i>

1336
01:26:44,785 --> 01:26:48,080
<i>But tonight,
you uncovered a nest of vipers</i>

1337
01:26:48,246 --> 01:26:50,665
<i>inside
the Detroit Police Department.</i>

1338
01:26:50,832 --> 01:26:55,170
<i>And in so doing,
you shed light
on an invaluable truth.</i>

1339
01:26:55,796 --> 01:26:57,255
Even the police,

1340
01:26:57,339 --> 01:27:01,343
the men and women
who swore to keep us safe,

1341
01:27:02,135 --> 01:27:03,637
they can be bribed.

1342
01:27:04,262 --> 01:27:07,140
They can be bought.

1343
01:27:08,767 --> 01:27:12,896
Machines, however,
are corruption free.

1344
01:27:13,855 --> 01:27:16,066
Americans could be
living in a country

1345
01:27:16,149 --> 01:27:19,486
where law enforcement
is not only efficient,

1346
01:27:19,820 --> 01:27:21,321
but incorruptible.

1347
01:27:22,656 --> 01:27:24,950
Thank you, Alex,
for all you've done.

1348
01:27:25,117 --> 01:27:26,827
And for all that you are.

1349
01:27:27,327 --> 01:27:30,497
<i>Detective Murphy
is currently
in critical condition.</i>

1350
01:27:31,164 --> 01:27:33,917
Our doctors
are working ceaselessly

1351
01:27:34,000 --> 01:27:36,753
but, at this time,
it is unclear
if he will survive.

1352
01:27:36,837 --> 01:27:37,963
(REPORTERS CLAMORING)

1353
01:27:38,046 --> 01:27:40,048
KELLY: <i>Ms. Kline,
how do you think the attempt</i>

1354
01:27:40,132 --> 01:27:42,008
<i>on Detective
Alex Murphy's life</i>

1355
01:27:42,092 --> 01:27:44,386
<i>will affect tomorrow's vote
for the Dreyfus Act?</i>

1356
01:27:44,469 --> 01:27:46,346
LIZ: <i>At this time,
Omnicorp's sole concern</i>

1357
01:27:46,430 --> 01:27:48,515
<i>is the full recovery
of Detective Murphy.</i>

1358
01:27:49,641 --> 01:27:51,810
<i>How many times
does Detective Murphy</i>

1359
01:27:51,893 --> 01:27:54,312
<i>have to give his life
for his country?</i>

1360
01:27:54,980 --> 01:27:59,818
<i>I sincerely hope the Senate
makes the right vote tomorrow</i>

1361
01:27:59,901 --> 01:28:04,489
<i>so that Alex Murphy's
sacrifices will not
have been in vain.</i>

1362
01:28:09,202 --> 01:28:11,455
OHIO SENATOR ON TV:
<i>Senator Dreyfus is my friend.</i>

1363
01:28:11,538 --> 01:28:14,332
<i>He has been
my mentor and my strength</i>

1364
01:28:14,416 --> 01:28:16,877
<i>in times of difficulty
on this floor.</i>

1365
01:28:17,377 --> 01:28:20,464
<i>But despite all that,
I work for the state of Ohio,</i>

1366
01:28:20,547 --> 01:28:23,675
<i>and the safety of its citizens
is my top priority.</i>

1367
01:28:24,050 --> 01:28:25,093
<i>So I vote yes.</i>

1368
01:28:25,260 --> 01:28:27,554
<i>The Dreyfus Act
must be repealed.</i>

1369
01:28:27,888 --> 01:28:30,056
That's us ahead,
39 to 10.

1370
01:28:30,223 --> 01:28:33,143
I spoke to the Senate
liaison and it looks
like it's in the bag,

1371
01:28:33,226 --> 01:28:36,313
but we still have to
tread carefully
with the politicians.

1372
01:28:36,396 --> 01:28:37,814
(NOVAK ELEMENT THEME SONG
PLAYING ON TV)

1373
01:28:37,898 --> 01:28:40,150
KELLY: <i>We're here live
at DPD headquarters</i>

1374
01:28:40,233 --> 01:28:42,986
<i>where moments ago,
Clara Murphy made
a shocking statement.</i>

1375
01:28:43,069 --> 01:28:44,279
POPE: What the hell?

1376
01:28:44,362 --> 01:28:49,409
<i>Omnicorp has denied
me and my son
access to Alex for weeks.</i>

1377
01:28:50,076 --> 01:28:51,912
<i>I demand to know why.</i>

1378
01:28:52,913 --> 01:28:57,918
<i>This treatment is inhuman
and somebody needs to be
held accountable.</i>

1379
01:28:59,127 --> 01:29:00,921
Oh, we're fucked.

1380
01:29:01,087 --> 01:29:02,464
No, we only need 12 votes.

1381
01:29:02,547 --> 01:29:04,049
She shouldn't make
much difference.

1382
01:29:04,216 --> 01:29:06,426
POPE: Yeah, but what about
after the vote?

1383
01:29:06,510 --> 01:29:08,345
I mean, those two should
not be allowed contact.

1384
01:29:08,428 --> 01:29:10,847
If she starts
putting ideas in his head...

1385
01:29:10,972 --> 01:29:13,642
Bring her in.
I'll handle the explanation.

1386
01:29:13,808 --> 01:29:15,268
POPE: And what about Alex?

1387
01:29:15,352 --> 01:29:17,604
You know, unfortunately,
we can't just keep him on ice.

1388
01:29:18,271 --> 01:29:20,815
LIZ: The shooting
at the station spooked
some of the politicians.

1389
01:29:20,899 --> 01:29:23,401
They're our clients.
We have to take care of them.

1390
01:29:23,568 --> 01:29:26,988
They're fine when a machine
is lowering the murder rate,

1391
01:29:27,072 --> 01:29:30,367
but when a man is
investigating city politics,
they get nervous.

1392
01:29:30,450 --> 01:29:32,827
All right. First off,
it's not a man, okay?

1393
01:29:32,911 --> 01:29:34,871
It's property of Omnicorp.

1394
01:29:34,955 --> 01:29:37,207
And politics are
the least of your concern.

1395
01:29:37,290 --> 01:29:38,959
I mean, this thing
solved its own murder.

1396
01:29:39,125 --> 01:29:41,503
How long till it
realizes you haven't been
on the level with it?

1397
01:29:41,586 --> 01:29:42,712
POPE: If that happens,

1398
01:29:42,796 --> 01:29:45,715
every journalist
in this country
is dying to speak to him.

1399
01:29:45,799 --> 01:29:47,759
I mean, we created a hero.

1400
01:29:48,301 --> 01:29:50,971
What happens
when he opens his mouth?

1401
01:29:54,474 --> 01:29:56,184
What's bigger than a hero?

1402
01:30:07,862 --> 01:30:09,155
Dead hero.

1403
01:30:13,493 --> 01:30:15,453
Get me Dr. Norton.

1404
01:30:24,504 --> 01:30:25,630
What is this, Raymond?

1405
01:30:26,756 --> 01:30:30,760
You have Mattox spying on me
and now this bullshit
about a "critical condition"?

1406
01:30:30,927 --> 01:30:33,638
You know and I know
Alex is fine!

1407
01:30:33,805 --> 01:30:34,973
Calm down.

1408
01:30:35,140 --> 01:30:36,641
Dennett.

1409
01:30:36,808 --> 01:30:37,976
Your work is so good,
I don't...

1410
01:30:38,059 --> 01:30:39,394
Well, now,
this is not about my work!

1411
01:30:39,477 --> 01:30:41,396
You saw the woman on TV!

1412
01:30:41,563 --> 01:30:43,690
This has to stop!

1413
01:30:45,525 --> 01:30:46,818
You're right.

1414
01:30:47,527 --> 01:30:49,529
But let me
ask you something, Dennett.

1415
01:30:49,696 --> 01:30:52,115
What kind of life
have we really
given Alex Murphy?

1416
01:30:52,198 --> 01:30:55,744
He's never gonna be
a normal man,
a father, a husband.

1417
01:30:55,827 --> 01:30:59,080
By the time we put
the other units on the
street, he's just...

1418
01:30:59,247 --> 01:31:00,332
Dennett.

1419
01:31:00,874 --> 01:31:02,125
(SIGHS HEAVILY)

1420
01:31:02,208 --> 01:31:03,710
Let's face it.

1421
01:31:04,544 --> 01:31:06,046
We failed him.

1422
01:31:07,505 --> 01:31:09,424
We failed Alex Murphy.

1423
01:31:09,507 --> 01:31:11,134
But I want you
to think about
the bigger picture

1424
01:31:11,217 --> 01:31:12,719
because that's what
we're talking about.

1425
01:31:12,844 --> 01:31:15,597
The work you've done
with him is gonna be
studied for decades.

1426
01:31:15,680 --> 01:31:17,891
You've changed
the face of history, Dennett.

1427
01:31:17,974 --> 01:31:22,270
No policeman is ever
going to die in
the line of duty again

1428
01:31:23,021 --> 01:31:24,564
because of you.

1429
01:31:26,232 --> 01:31:27,692
You think about that.

1430
01:31:36,201 --> 01:31:40,163
I want that family
taken care of

1431
01:31:40,246 --> 01:31:41,748
beyond their wildest dreams.

1432
01:31:41,790 --> 01:31:43,875
We owe them that.
I agree.

1433
01:31:44,626 --> 01:31:47,962
I want full funding.
Ten years.

1434
01:31:48,380 --> 01:31:50,048
New staff, all my own people.

1435
01:31:50,215 --> 01:31:51,758
Fantastic.

1436
01:31:52,467 --> 01:31:53,468
Deal.

1437
01:32:03,853 --> 01:32:05,355
Hey. What's going on?

1438
01:32:05,438 --> 01:32:07,524
Security's here.
They're clearing everyone out.

1439
01:32:07,607 --> 01:32:09,359
They're not waking him up.

1440
01:32:09,442 --> 01:32:11,319
Whatever you do,
don't leave him alone.

1441
01:32:11,403 --> 01:32:12,946
What do you mean
they're not waking him up?

1442
01:32:14,739 --> 01:32:16,157
SENATE LEADER ON TV:
<i>The voting period has ended.</i>

1443
01:32:16,241 --> 01:32:18,827
<i>The clerks have
tabulated the results.</i>

1444
01:32:18,910 --> 01:32:20,954
<i>The yeas are 63.</i>

1445
01:32:21,037 --> 01:32:23,748
<i>The nays are 22.</i>

1446
01:32:23,832 --> 01:32:26,334
<i>A majority of senators have
voted in the affirmative.</i>

1447
01:32:26,418 --> 01:32:30,171
<i>The Dreyfus Act has been
repealed by Congress.</i>

1448
01:32:30,255 --> 01:32:31,548
(PEOPLE APPLAUDING)

1449
01:32:34,592 --> 01:32:35,593
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

1450
01:32:35,677 --> 01:32:38,221
God, you guys are slow,
like a bunch of girls.

1451
01:32:38,304 --> 01:32:39,389
This is Mattox.

1452
01:32:39,472 --> 01:32:40,849
SELLARS: <i>Dennett's on board.</i>

1453
01:32:40,932 --> 01:32:42,517
It's about time.

1454
01:32:47,605 --> 01:32:48,732
Call it.

1455
01:32:49,482 --> 01:32:50,900
<i>Get it done.</i>

1456
01:32:51,901 --> 01:32:53,319
My pleasure.

1457
01:32:55,488 --> 01:32:57,157
(DOORBELL CHIMES)

1458
01:33:02,036 --> 01:33:04,247
Mrs. Murphy...
You can come here
as much as you want.

1459
01:33:04,330 --> 01:33:07,584
You can threaten me.
You can sue me.
You can take my home.

1460
01:33:07,667 --> 01:33:10,587
But I am not gonna stop
till I see my husband.
Do you understand that?

1461
01:33:10,879 --> 01:33:13,631
Mr. Sellars would
very much like to see you.

1462
01:33:15,175 --> 01:33:16,676
Is Alex okay?

1463
01:33:16,926 --> 01:33:20,388
He has important information
to share with you.
Will you accompany me?

1464
01:33:20,472 --> 01:33:21,681
(SIGHS)

1465
01:33:22,724 --> 01:33:23,892
David.

1466
01:33:25,602 --> 01:33:27,854
We gotta go.
Can you grab your coat?

1467
01:33:27,937 --> 01:33:29,105
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

1468
01:33:29,189 --> 01:33:30,190
Hey!

1469
01:33:30,273 --> 01:33:31,316
DR. NORTON:
<i>I'm in the elevator,</i>
<i>on my way down.</i>

1470
01:33:31,399 --> 01:33:32,942
I need access to the lab.

1471
01:33:33,026 --> 01:33:34,652
That's insane.
They're still here.

1472
01:33:34,736 --> 01:33:36,446
<i>Distract them.</i>

1473
01:33:36,529 --> 01:33:37,655
Okay.

1474
01:33:38,865 --> 01:33:39,908
I cannot...

1475
01:33:39,991 --> 01:33:42,160
MALE SECURITY GUARD:
There's a lady in here
going hysterical.

1476
01:33:42,243 --> 01:33:44,120
She will not let us in.
She's got the codes
for the door.

1477
01:33:44,204 --> 01:33:45,872
I repeat,
she will not let us in.

1478
01:33:45,955 --> 01:33:48,249
Lady, you need to
let us in there now.
We have to get in there.

1479
01:33:48,333 --> 01:33:49,834
Are you not understanding
what I'm saying?

1480
01:33:49,918 --> 01:33:52,754
Do you wanna be responsible
for the deaths of everyone
in this building?

1481
01:33:53,046 --> 01:33:54,422
Hey! Stop!

1482
01:33:54,506 --> 01:33:56,216
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

1483
01:33:58,593 --> 01:33:59,719
Don't shoot!

1484
01:33:59,803 --> 01:34:01,179
Step outside.

1485
01:34:07,644 --> 01:34:09,312
Unlock the transmitter!

1486
01:34:10,688 --> 01:34:11,689
KIM: Transmitter
unlocked!

1487
01:34:19,155 --> 01:34:21,032
Send in Mrs. Murphy, please.

1488
01:34:21,115 --> 01:34:22,575
RECEPTIONIST OVER INTERCOM:
<i>Right away, sir.</i>

1489
01:34:24,744 --> 01:34:25,995
DR. NORTON:
<i>Wake him up!</i>

1490
01:34:26,412 --> 01:34:29,499
Alex! Alex!

1491
01:34:29,916 --> 01:34:33,086
Alex, it's Dr. Norton,
you have to wake up!

1492
01:34:33,169 --> 01:34:34,379
Alex, can you hear me?

1493
01:34:35,922 --> 01:34:37,674
These men are here
to kill us.

1494
01:34:37,757 --> 01:34:40,218
They're here to kill us,
for chrissakes!

1495
01:34:45,098 --> 01:34:46,808
SELLARS:
<i>Mrs. Murphy, last night,</i>

1496
01:34:46,891 --> 01:34:48,893
Alex had a psychotic break.

1497
01:34:48,977 --> 01:34:53,273
He killed an unarmed colleague
and later suffered a seizure.

1498
01:34:54,399 --> 01:34:55,900
We did everything,

1499
01:34:55,984 --> 01:34:58,903
everything, we could,
but the doctors
couldn't save him.

1500
01:35:00,363 --> 01:35:02,407
Very sorry, Mrs. Murphy.

1501
01:35:02,699 --> 01:35:05,243
We're going to be making
the announcement shortly.

1502
01:35:05,702 --> 01:35:08,162
You shut me down.
I was about to
get a confession.

1503
01:35:08,788 --> 01:35:10,456
Mattox shut you down.

1504
01:35:11,791 --> 01:35:14,669
I've removed your transmitter
so he won't do it again.

1505
01:35:15,086 --> 01:35:17,255
Sellars can't afford
to wake you up.

1506
01:35:18,298 --> 01:35:20,425
He sent these guys
to pull the plug.

1507
01:35:20,884 --> 01:35:24,387
He wants you dead, Alex.
Do you understand?

1508
01:35:24,554 --> 01:35:26,389
Sorry. If there's
anything we can do

1509
01:35:26,472 --> 01:35:27,807
for you and David,
we'll do it.

1510
01:35:27,974 --> 01:35:30,101
I want nothing from you.

1511
01:35:31,060 --> 01:35:32,353
I understand.

1512
01:35:32,937 --> 01:35:35,231
You stay out of our lives.

1513
01:35:36,649 --> 01:35:37,859
You and your company.

1514
01:35:38,151 --> 01:35:40,028
If that's what
you think is best.

1515
01:35:40,987 --> 01:35:42,447
There's one more thing.

1516
01:35:42,530 --> 01:35:45,366
I think it would be
to the benefit of everyone,
especially David

1517
01:35:45,450 --> 01:35:47,660
if we kept
this matter private.

1518
01:35:47,911 --> 01:35:50,455
We don't wanna
damage Alex's legacy.

1519
01:35:53,124 --> 01:35:54,959
DR. NORTON:
<i>Alex! Alex!</i>

1520
01:35:55,335 --> 01:35:56,961
I can fix this!

1521
01:35:57,045 --> 01:35:58,504
You lied to me.

1522
01:35:58,588 --> 01:35:59,839
You lied to my wife.

1523
01:35:59,923 --> 01:36:01,549
You're working for the people
that are trying to kill me.

1524
01:36:01,633 --> 01:36:02,884
You want me
to trust you, Doctor?

1525
01:36:02,967 --> 01:36:05,011
Alex, I can go to the press!

1526
01:36:06,429 --> 01:36:09,015
Alex, I can tell them
the whole story!

1527
01:36:09,307 --> 01:36:10,767
Alex!

1528
01:36:11,309 --> 01:36:13,227
Listen to me, please!

1529
01:36:14,228 --> 01:36:17,523
Alex! Alex!

1530
01:36:29,160 --> 01:36:30,203
What the hell?

1531
01:36:32,705 --> 01:36:34,415
(TIRES SCREECHING)
(HORNS HONKING)

1532
01:36:38,586 --> 01:36:39,963
Keep all our systems
at green light,

1533
01:36:40,046 --> 01:36:42,131
and for chrissakes,
get Sellars on the phone.

1534
01:36:42,215 --> 01:36:43,216
MAN ON RADIO: <i>Roger that.</i>

1535
01:36:43,299 --> 01:36:45,259
Damn, damn, damn, damn, damn!

1536
01:36:46,594 --> 01:36:48,179
Look at this city.

1537
01:36:50,014 --> 01:36:51,557
So beautiful.

1538
01:36:52,558 --> 01:36:55,228
It's become so peaceful.

1539
01:36:58,022 --> 01:36:59,357
I wish

1540
01:37:00,358 --> 01:37:02,610
I had some good news
for Detroit.

1541
01:37:03,111 --> 01:37:04,862
I have very sad news.

1542
01:37:05,029 --> 01:37:07,699
Despite our best efforts
to save him,

1543
01:37:07,991 --> 01:37:10,451
Alex Murphy passed away
just hours ago.

1544
01:37:10,868 --> 01:37:12,161
Alex Murphy was...
(DOOR OPENING)

1545
01:37:12,245 --> 01:37:13,454
MALE SECURITY GUARD:
Mr. Sellars.

1546
01:37:13,871 --> 01:37:15,456
What is it?
Mattox just called.

1547
01:37:16,040 --> 01:37:17,875
We need you to
come with us now.

1548
01:37:24,173 --> 01:37:25,967
Ma'am, I need you to
turn around and go
the other way, please.

1549
01:37:26,092 --> 01:37:28,094
What are you talking about?
We have
a security situation here.

1550
01:37:28,177 --> 01:37:29,595
I need you to turn around
and go the other way.

1551
01:37:29,679 --> 01:37:31,556
Sir, there's a car outside
that's supposed to...

1552
01:37:31,639 --> 01:37:33,266
That area is locked down.
Now go.

1553
01:37:33,349 --> 01:37:35,018
What's happening?
I said go!

1554
01:37:35,351 --> 01:37:37,353
I wanna talk to Mr. Sellars.

1555
01:37:40,273 --> 01:37:41,357
Mr. Sellars.

1556
01:37:41,524 --> 01:37:43,484
How close
is that helicopter?
About 10 minutes, sir.

1557
01:38:01,335 --> 01:38:02,587
Excuse me.
Yes?

1558
01:38:02,754 --> 01:38:05,089
I need to speak with
Sergeant Jack Lewis.

1559
01:38:05,256 --> 01:38:06,466
It's an emergency.

1560
01:38:06,632 --> 01:38:08,259
Stand by. Mr. Sellars.

1561
01:38:08,718 --> 01:38:10,428
Apparently
there's a Clara Murphy
in the lobby.

1562
01:38:10,595 --> 01:38:13,931
Raymond, if she sees him,
we are dead in the water.

1563
01:38:14,098 --> 01:38:16,434
What do you wanna do?
Bring Mrs. Murphy up here.

1564
01:38:16,601 --> 01:38:17,685
MALE SECURITY GUARD: Yes, sir.

1565
01:38:18,519 --> 01:38:20,146
(SIRENS WAILING)

1566
01:38:21,606 --> 01:38:24,400
Norton said they may be
using drones for protection.

1567
01:38:24,567 --> 01:38:26,611
So whatever you do,
do not draw your weapons.

1568
01:38:26,778 --> 01:38:29,405
They won't shoot
if we're unarmed. Clear?

1569
01:38:29,489 --> 01:38:30,490
Clear.
Clear.

1570
01:38:46,881 --> 01:38:48,257
MALE SECURITY GUARD:
Hold it right there.

1571
01:38:49,258 --> 01:38:50,259
Don't move.

1572
01:38:54,013 --> 01:38:57,350
This is private property.
You are not authorized
to be here!

1573
01:38:58,851 --> 01:39:00,144
(GROANING)

1574
01:39:01,270 --> 01:39:03,606
I'd put those guns down now
if I were you.

1575
01:39:03,773 --> 01:39:05,441
Stand down.
All right, man, we're good.

1576
01:39:06,359 --> 01:39:07,735
(REVVING)
(TIRES SCREECHING)

1577
01:39:48,359 --> 01:39:49,944
(SIRENS WAILING)

1578
01:39:51,904 --> 01:39:53,239
Head to the lower level.

1579
01:39:54,866 --> 01:39:55,867
MALE SECURITY GUARD:
Hold up, hold up!

1580
01:39:55,992 --> 01:39:57,201
Ram it!

1581
01:40:00,413 --> 01:40:01,664
(GRUNTS)

1582
01:40:25,813 --> 01:40:27,940
(PANTING)

1583
01:40:33,362 --> 01:40:34,697
(GRUNTING)

1584
01:40:38,618 --> 01:40:39,952
(STRAINING)

1585
01:40:57,470 --> 01:40:58,763
Gun it.

1586
01:41:00,223 --> 01:41:01,807
Go, go, go! Now!

1587
01:41:06,229 --> 01:41:07,438
(GROANING)

1588
01:41:17,782 --> 01:41:19,283
Alex, run!

1589
01:41:20,117 --> 01:41:22,161
MAN: Omnicorp Security!
Drop your weapons!

1590
01:41:22,328 --> 01:41:24,247
ED-209 OVER SPEAKER:
<i>Drop your weapon.</i>

1591
01:41:24,413 --> 01:41:27,208
<i>Keep your hands
above your head
and no one will be harmed.</i>

1592
01:41:42,473 --> 01:41:43,599
What's going on?

1593
01:41:43,683 --> 01:41:45,935
Mrs. Murphy, I want you to
listen to me carefully.

1594
01:41:46,102 --> 01:41:48,604
The organic part of
your husband Alex is dead.

1595
01:41:48,688 --> 01:41:50,815
The robotic part of him
is malfunctioning,

1596
01:41:50,898 --> 01:41:51,983
and he's shooting up
the building.

1597
01:41:52,066 --> 01:41:54,860
So we've gotta get
you and your son
out of here right away.

1598
01:41:55,027 --> 01:41:56,570
I gotta take this call.

1599
01:41:57,863 --> 01:41:59,448
He just left the lobby
and he's headed our way.

1600
01:41:59,532 --> 01:42:01,075
MATTOX: <i>Roger that, sir.</i>

1601
01:42:01,492 --> 01:42:04,537
Don't shoot. My robot.
You just flank.
Got it.

1602
01:42:04,704 --> 01:42:05,955
Tin Man.

1603
01:42:08,708 --> 01:42:09,917
Tin Man.

1604
01:42:10,960 --> 01:42:12,211
Tin Man.

1605
01:42:12,795 --> 01:42:13,963
Oh, there it is.

1606
01:42:14,630 --> 01:42:16,007
You look like crap.

1607
01:42:18,634 --> 01:42:19,802
What's the matter?

1608
01:42:19,969 --> 01:42:21,178
Can't shoot?

1609
01:42:22,972 --> 01:42:24,056
Huh?

1610
01:42:24,807 --> 01:42:26,892
What were you thinking?
This isn't a drill.

1611
01:42:26,976 --> 01:42:27,977
You're a robot.

1612
01:42:28,185 --> 01:42:30,396
I'm a red asset.
Wrote that myself.

1613
01:42:30,855 --> 01:42:32,148
What do you think?

1614
01:42:32,565 --> 01:42:35,401
Come on, Tin Man,
just pull the trigger.

1615
01:42:35,568 --> 01:42:36,569
Pull it.

1616
01:42:37,361 --> 01:42:38,446
You can run.

1617
01:42:38,988 --> 01:42:39,989
Go on.

1618
01:42:40,239 --> 01:42:41,365
Run.

1619
01:42:41,824 --> 01:42:42,950
Run!

1620
01:42:43,284 --> 01:42:45,119
There you go. Run.

1621
01:42:45,578 --> 01:42:46,912
Run. Run!

1622
01:42:47,830 --> 01:42:49,206
(SCREAMING)

1623
01:42:50,082 --> 01:42:51,500
Whoo!

1624
01:42:51,584 --> 01:42:53,711
Stings like a bitch,
don't it?

1625
01:42:53,878 --> 01:42:57,173
Aren't you lucky
I didn't have my gun
set to "kill"?

1626
01:42:57,256 --> 01:42:58,341
(GROANING)

1627
01:42:58,424 --> 01:42:59,759
Hey, listen.

1628
01:43:00,217 --> 01:43:01,802
This isn't personal.

1629
01:43:02,845 --> 01:43:04,597
Well, maybe a little.

1630
01:43:06,349 --> 01:43:08,184
I'm gonna put you
out of your misery.

1631
01:43:08,351 --> 01:43:09,393
(GROANS)

1632
01:43:10,770 --> 01:43:12,229
(BOTH GROAN)

1633
01:43:19,904 --> 01:43:21,364
LEAD OMNICORP AGENT:
<i>Helicopter's approaching.</i>

1634
01:43:21,447 --> 01:43:22,698
Mr. Sellars boards first.

1635
01:43:22,782 --> 01:43:25,743
No, no, no. Mrs. Murphy,
you and your son
can get on first.

1636
01:43:28,162 --> 01:43:29,497
(GROANING)

1637
01:43:31,165 --> 01:43:32,458
Officer down.

1638
01:43:32,541 --> 01:43:33,667
Mechanical room.

1639
01:43:33,751 --> 01:43:35,336
Omnicorp Building.

1640
01:43:35,503 --> 01:43:37,380
DISPATCH OVER RADIO:
<i>Roger that. EMS. on the way.</i>

1641
01:43:39,006 --> 01:43:40,591
You're gonna be okay, Jack.

1642
01:43:40,674 --> 01:43:41,926
It's nonfatal.

1643
01:43:42,009 --> 01:43:43,594
Go. Go.

1644
01:43:44,804 --> 01:43:47,598
PILOT: Omni-LZ Helo-1
on approach to deck.

1645
01:43:54,355 --> 01:43:55,356
What's that?

1646
01:43:57,274 --> 01:43:58,401
He's got a gun!
What?

1647
01:43:58,567 --> 01:43:59,568
Pull up! Pull up!

1648
01:44:04,532 --> 01:44:06,826
What the hell is he doing?
Sorry, sir. I don't know.

1649
01:44:12,373 --> 01:44:13,374
Alex?

1650
01:44:13,541 --> 01:44:14,542
Dad?

1651
01:44:17,962 --> 01:44:19,380
Clara, David.

1652
01:44:20,381 --> 01:44:21,549
Whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa.

1653
01:44:21,632 --> 01:44:22,633
Wait.

1654
01:44:23,717 --> 01:44:25,594
Get out of the way.
Alex, put down the gun.

1655
01:44:25,761 --> 01:44:27,847
Clara, take David
and get out of the way now!

1656
01:44:29,723 --> 01:44:31,100
Raymond Sellars,
you're under arrest

1657
01:44:31,183 --> 01:44:32,935
for the attempted murder
of a police officer.

1658
01:44:36,647 --> 01:44:39,150
Are you here to cuff me?
All right.

1659
01:44:39,942 --> 01:44:41,402
Go 'head, cuff me.

1660
01:44:42,611 --> 01:44:45,197
You can't.
You're not programmed
that way.

1661
01:44:45,281 --> 01:44:46,782
If you go against
the program,

1662
01:44:46,866 --> 01:44:48,701
the entire system
shuts down, so.

1663
01:44:48,868 --> 01:44:50,953
You don't even have
a warrant. We'll
overlook this little...

1664
01:44:51,120 --> 01:44:53,205
Get down on the ground
and put your hands
behind your back.

1665
01:44:53,372 --> 01:44:54,373
I'm just from marketing.

1666
01:44:54,540 --> 01:44:56,876
Now!
Okay, yep, yep, yep. Yep.

1667
01:44:57,042 --> 01:44:59,211
Alex, we need to
work together here.

1668
01:44:59,378 --> 01:45:02,465
Because I'm the only one
with the technology
to keep you alive.

1669
01:45:03,591 --> 01:45:05,217
Dead or alive,
you're coming with me.

1670
01:45:08,471 --> 01:45:09,889
(GRUNTING)

1671
01:45:11,348 --> 01:45:12,349
All right.

1672
01:45:12,516 --> 01:45:13,517
Weapon.

1673
01:45:15,186 --> 01:45:18,314
Alex, honestly,
I mean you no harm.

1674
01:45:18,481 --> 01:45:20,774
If I wanted to,
I could have killed you
a long time ago.

1675
01:45:20,941 --> 01:45:22,818
I just aim this
right at your head
and blow it off.

1676
01:45:22,902 --> 01:45:24,737
Sellars, please! Don't!

1677
01:45:24,904 --> 01:45:27,448
I mean, if I wanted to,
I could just aim this
at your little family

1678
01:45:28,782 --> 01:45:30,367
and I could just
kill them too.

1679
01:45:30,493 --> 01:45:32,161
And really, there's nothing
you could do about it

1680
01:45:32,244 --> 01:45:34,246
because, let's face it,

1681
01:45:34,872 --> 01:45:36,207
you're a robot.

1682
01:45:36,832 --> 01:45:38,292
Do you understand that?

1683
01:45:42,546 --> 01:45:43,547
Alex.

1684
01:45:45,382 --> 01:45:46,383
(BOTH GROAN)

1685
01:45:46,717 --> 01:45:47,968
Dad!

1686
01:45:52,097 --> 01:45:53,349
(WHISPERING) Baby.

1687
01:45:58,938 --> 01:46:00,022
Hey.

1688
01:46:01,649 --> 01:46:02,650
Hey.

1689
01:46:03,150 --> 01:46:05,152
Everything's gonna be
all right.

1690
01:46:06,111 --> 01:46:08,364
Everything's gonna be
all right.

1691
01:46:14,995 --> 01:46:16,539
(CLARA SOBBING)

1692
01:46:42,982 --> 01:46:44,608
(HEART BEATING)

1693
01:46:58,247 --> 01:46:59,999
How you feeling, Alex?

1694
01:47:01,917 --> 01:47:03,043
I'm ready.

1695
01:47:40,831 --> 01:47:42,207
He's ready.
(SIGHS)

1696
01:48:16,325 --> 01:48:17,493
NOVAK: There's still no word

1697
01:48:17,576 --> 01:48:20,579
from Omnicorp
parent company, OCP.

1698
01:48:21,497 --> 01:48:25,250
And although
the government says they
are rebuilding Alex Murphy,

1699
01:48:25,334 --> 01:48:28,045
rumors continue to swirl
about his condition.

1700
01:48:28,128 --> 01:48:32,675
But we have obtained
exclusive video
taken by cell phone

1701
01:48:32,758 --> 01:48:35,177
that shows
the people of Detroit

1702
01:48:35,260 --> 01:48:37,346
may have Alex Murphy
back on the streets

1703
01:48:37,429 --> 01:48:39,014
sooner than they think.

1704
01:48:41,058 --> 01:48:42,559
The real tragedy here

1705
01:48:42,643 --> 01:48:47,439
is that our president chose
to uphold the Dreyfus Act.

1706
01:48:48,816 --> 01:48:53,570
Now, I have no doubt
he was manipulated
